Net: the level case for higher yields is intact and modestly reinforced — inflation pressure (stale but unrebutted), term premium rising on real supply/composition grounds now corroborated by balance-sheet runoff continuing, with financial conditions neutral rather than offsetting. This is not a stronger call than before, but it's not weaker either; the gap that could have flipped term_premium (financial-conditions-driven flight to quality) didn't show up. I hold the existing modest up-yield duration position rather than resize meaningfully, given panel is directionally consistent but no driver strengthened enough to add conviction, and inflation's staleness caps how hard I lean.</notes>
